TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditForm
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Renders a form element that cascades an <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditForm.EditContext" /> to descendants.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AdditionalAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a collection of additional attributes that will be applied to the created <c>form</c> element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EditContext
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supplies the edit context explicitly. If using this parameter, do not
            also supply <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditForm.Model" />, since the model value will be taken
            from the <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditContext.Model" /> property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Model
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the top-level model object for the form. An edit context will
            be constructed for this model. If using this parameter, do not also supply
            a value for <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditForm.EditContext" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the content to be rendered inside this <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditForm" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnSubmit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             A callback that will be invoked when the form is submitted.
            
             If using this parameter, you are responsible for triggering any validation
             manually, e.g., by calling <see cref="M:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditContext.Validate" />.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnValidSubmit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A callback that will be invoked when the form is submitted and the
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditForm.EditContext" /> is determined to be valid.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnInvalidSubmit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A callback that will be invoked when the form is submitted and the
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditForm.EditContext" /> is determined to be invalid.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

            content based on the current value of <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting.IHostingEnvironment.EnvironmentName" />.
            If the environment is not listed in the specified <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Names" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Include" />,
            or if it is in <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Exclude" />, the content will not be rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: names
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of environment names in which the content should be rendered.
            If the current environment is also in the <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.EnvironmentTagHelper.Exclude" /> list, the content will not be rendered.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The specified environment names are compared case insensitively to the current value of
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting.IHostingEnvironment.EnvironmentName" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: include

            </summary>
            <remarks>

            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting.IHostingEnvironment.EnvironmentName" />.

BoundAttributes.Name: exclude

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format string (see https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/txafckwd.aspx) used to format the
            <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.For" /> result. Sets the generated "value" attribute to that formatted string.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Not used if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is
            <c>checkbox</c>, <c>password</c>, or <c>radio</c>. That is, <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> is used when calling
            <see cref="M:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IHtmlGenerator.GenerateTextBox(Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ViewContext,Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ModelExplorer,System.String,System.Object,System.String,System.Object)" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The type of the <input> element.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases. Also used to determine the <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IHtmlGenerator" />
            helper to call and the default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> value. A default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> is not calculated
            if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is <c>checkbox</c>,
            <c>hidden</c>, <c>password</c>, or <c>radio</c>.

            valid with an empty <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ModelExpression.Name" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

            if <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" /> is "radio". Must not be <c>null</c> in that case.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: collision
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures how the popup should behave when it cannot be properly displayed and fully visible, if its origin and position settings are obeyed.Valid values are: "fit", "flip", "flip fit" and "fit flip". "Fit" allows the popup to be shifted (moved) until it is fully visible. "Flip" allows the popup to switch its position, according to its anchor. If two words are used, the first one applies to the horizontal dimension and the second one - to the vertical dimension. If one word is used, the setting is applied to both dimensions.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: origin
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: position

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the editing functionality of the Breadcrumb will be enabled/disabled.If the option is enabled the path will be editable. Clicking in an empty area of the component will trigger editing mode. Editing mode shows an input showing the value of the component enabling the end user to type a new path.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: gap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: navigational
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the navigation functionality of the Breadcrumb will be enabled/disabled.When navigational is set to false, automatic navigation (changing url location) is disabled by default. In this state, the click event will be prevented and navigation will occur only if programmatic navigation is implemented.When navigational is set to true, the url (path) will be automatically added to the href attribute of the rendered links. In this state, the click event will trigger navigation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: icon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines a name of an existing icon in the Kendo UI theme sprite. The icon will be applied as background image of a span element inside the Button. The span element can be added automatically by the widget, or an existing element can be used, if it has a k-icon CSS class applied. For a list of available icon names, please refer to the Icons demo.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines a URL, which will be used for an img element inside the Button. The URL can be relative or absolute. In case it is relative, it will be evaluated with relation to the web page URL.The img element can be added automatically by the widget, or an existing element can be used, if it has a k-image CSS class applied.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: sprite-css-class
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines a CSS class (or multiple classes separated by spaces), which will be used for applying a background image to a span element inside the Button. In case you want to use an icon from the Kendo UI theme sprite background image, it is easier to use the icon property.The span element can be added automatically by the widget, or an existing element can be used, if it has a k-sprite CSS class applied.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template to be used for rendering the cells in "week" column. By default, the widget renders the calculated week of the year.  The properties available in the data object are: currentDate - returns the first date of the current week. or weekNumber - calculated week number.. These properties can be used in the template to make additional calculations.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            The maximum number of ticks, labels and grid lines to display. Applicable for date category axis. You can combine this property with a bigger value of the maxDateGroups property to increase the number of rendered data points in the Chart without drawing too many labels, ticks, and grid lines.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: min
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The first date displayed on the category date axis. By default, the minimum date is the same as the first category. This is often used in combination with the categoryAxis.min and categoryAxis.roundToBaseUnit options to set up a fixed date range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The unique axis name. Used to associate a series with a category axis using the series.categoryAxis option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: pane
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the pane that the category axis should be rendered in. The axis will be rendered in the first (default) pane if not set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: reverse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the category axis direction will be reversed. By default categories are listed from left to right and from bottom to top.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: round-to-base-unit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will round the first and last date to the nearest base unit.The roundToBaseUnit option will be ignored if series.type is set to "bar", "column", "boxPlot", "ohlc", "candlestick" or "waterfall".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: start-angle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The angle (degrees) of the first category on the axis.Angles increase clockwise and zero is to the left. Negative values are acceptable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the category axis. By default the category axis is visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: week-start-day
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The week start day when categoryAxis.baseUnit is set to "weeks".The supported values are: kendo.days.Sunday - equal to 0; kendo.days.Monday - equal to 1; kendo.days.Tuesday - equal to 2; kendo.days.Wednesday - equal to 3; kendo.days.Thursday - equal to 4; kendo.days.Friday - equal to 5 or kendo.days.Saturday - equal to 6.
            </summary>

<summary>

Such browsers are IE version 9 and lower and Safari.The developer is responsible for implementing the server-side proxy.The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType: The MIME type of the file; base64: The base-64 encoded file content or fileName: The file name, as requested by the caller.. The proxy should return the decoded file with set "Content-Disposition" header.

BoundAttributes.Name: position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The position of the labels. "above" - the label is positioned at the top of the marker. Applicable for series that render points, incl. bubble.; "below" - the label is positioned at the bottom of the marker. Applicable for series that render points, incl. bubble.; "center" - the label is positioned at the point center. Applicable for bar, column, donut, pie, funnel, radarColumn and waterfall series.; "insideBase" - the label is positioned inside, near the base of the bar. Applicable for bar, column and waterfall series.; "insideEnd" - the label is positioned inside, near the end of the point. Applicable for bar, column, donut, pie, radarColumn and waterfall series.; "left" - the label is positioned to the left of the marker. Applicable for series that render points, incl. bubble.; "outsideEnd" - the label is positioned outside, near the end of the point. Applicable for bar, column, donut, pie, radarColumn and waterfall series. Not applicable for stacked series.; "right" - the label is positioned to the right of the marker. Applicable for series that render points, incl. bubble.; "top" - the label is positioned at the top of the segment. Applicable for funnel series.; "bottom" - the label is positioned at the bottom of the segment. Applicable for funnel series. or "auto" - the from and to labels area positioned at the top/bottom(rangeArea series) or left/right(verticalRangeArea series) so that they are outside the filled area. Applicable for rangeArea and verticalRangeArea series..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: collision
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures how the popup should behave when it cannot be properly displayed and fully visible, if its origin and position settings are obeyed.Valid values are: "fit", "flip", "flip fit" and "fit flip". "Fit" allows the popup to be shifted (moved) until it is fully visible. "Flip" allows the popup to switch its position, according to its anchor. If two words are used, the first one applies to the horizontal dimension and the second one - to the vertical dimension. If one word is used, the setting is applied to both dimensions.
            </summary>

            </summary>

            The DOM element to which the ContextMenu will be appended. The element needs to be relatively positioned.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: close-on-click
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies that sub menus should close after item selection (provided they won't navigate).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: copy-anchor-styles
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Copies and uses the styles from the anchor.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: filter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies ContextMenu filter selector - the ContextMenu will only be shown on items that satisfy the provided selector.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: hover-delay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the delay in ms before the sub menus are opened/closed - used to avoid accidental closure on leaving.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: popup-collision
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies how ContextMenu should adjust to screen boundaries. By default the strategy is "fit" for a sub menu with a horizontal parent or the root menu, meaning it will move to fit in screen boundaries in all directions, and "fit flip" for a sub menu with vertical parent, meaning it will fit vertically and flip over its parent horizontally. You can also switch off the screen boundary detection completely if you set the popupCollision to false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: show-on
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the event or events on which ContextMenu should open. By default ContextMenu will show on contextmenu event on desktop and hold event on touch devices. Could be any pointer/mouse/touch event, also several, separated by spaces.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the element on which ContextMenu should open. The default element is the document body.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: orientation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the orientation in which the menu items will be ordered
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: aggregate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the aggregate function.The supported aggregates are: "average"; "count"; "max"; "min" or "sum".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: field
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field which will be used to calculate the aggregates.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: field
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field to which the filter operator is applied.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: logic
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The logical operation to use when the filter.filters option is set.The supported values are: "and" or "or".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: operator
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The filter operator (comparison).The supported operators are: "eq" (equal to); "neq" (not equal to); "isnull" (is equal to null); "isnotnull" (is not equal to null); "lt" (less than); "lte" (less than or equal to); "gt" (greater than); "gte" (greater than or equal to); "startswith"; "endswith"; "contains"; "doesnotcontain"; "isempty" or "isnotempty". The last five are supported only for string fields.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The value to which the field is compared. The value has to be of the same type as the field.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: operator-handler
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The filter operator (comparison) function name.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: compare
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A JavaScript function which is used to compare the groups (refer to sortable for sorting the items of the groups). It has the same signature as the compare function accepted by Array.sort.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: direction
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The sort order of the group.The supported values are: "asc" (ascending order) or "desc" (descending order). The default sort order is ascending.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: field
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field to group by.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: default-value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the default value which will be used for the field when a new model instance is created. The default settings depend on the type of the field. The default value for "string" is "", for "number" is 0, and for "date" is new Date() (today).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the type of the field. The available options are "string", "number", "boolean", "date" and "object". The default is "string".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: editable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies if the field is editable or not. The default value is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: parse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: nullable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: from
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: required

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: min
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: max
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the data source would automatically save any changed data items by calling the sync method. By default, changes are not automatically saved.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: batch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will batch CRUD operation requests. For example, updating two data items would cause one HTTP request instead of two. By default, the data source makes a HTTP request for every CRUD operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: in-place-sort
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the original Array used as data will be sorted when sorting operation is performed. This setting supported only with local data, bound to a JavaScript array via the data option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: group-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will treat groups as items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: offline-storage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The offline storage key or custom offline storage implementation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page of data which the data source will return when the view method is invoked or request from the remote service.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page-size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of data items per page. The property has no default value. That is why to use paging, make sure some pageSize value is set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: accent-folding-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures whether diacritic filtering should be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source is populated from a JavaScript array or a remote service, a data item is inserted, updated or removed, the data items are paged, sorted, filtered, or grouped.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the change event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a request to the remote service fails.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-push
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source receives a push notification or the pushCreate, pushUpdate, or pushDestroy methods are called.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the push event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-end
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a remote service request is finished.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestEnd event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-start
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source makes a remote service request.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.It is possible to prevent the remote request. To achieve this, execute e.preventDefault() in the handler function.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestStart event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired after the data source saves data item changes. The data source saves the data item changes when the sync method is called.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the sync event.</param>

<summary>
            Specifies the paper size of the PDF document. The default "auto" means paper size is determined by content.Supported values: A predefined size: "A4", "A3" etc; An array of two numbers specifying the width and height in points (1pt = 1/72in) or An array of two strings specifying the width and height in units. Supported units are "mm", "cm", "in" and "pt"..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of the server side proxy which will stream the file to the end user.A proxy will be used when the browser is not capable of saving files locally, for example, Internet Explorer 9 and Safari.The developer is responsible for implementing the server-side proxy.The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType: The MIME type of the file; base64: The base-64 encoded file content or fileName: The file name, as requested by the caller.. The proxy should return the decoded file with the "Content-Disposition" header set toattachment; filename="<fileName.pdf>".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A name or keyword indicating where to display the document returned from the proxy.If you want to display the document in a new window or iframe, the proxy should set the "Content-Disposition" header to inline; filename="<fileName.pdf>".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the data source would automatically save any changed data items by calling the sync method. By default, changes are not automatically saved.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: batch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will batch CRUD operation requests. For example, updating two data items would cause one HTTP request instead of two. By default, the data source makes a HTTP request for every CRUD operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: in-place-sort
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the original Array used as data will be sorted when sorting operation is performed. This setting supported only with local data, bound to a JavaScript array via the data option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: group-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will treat groups as items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: offline-storage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The offline storage key or custom offline storage implementation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page of data which the data source will return when the view method is invoked or request from the remote service.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page-size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of data items per page. The property has no default value. That is why to use paging, make sure some pageSize value is set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: accent-folding-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures whether diacritic filtering should be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source is populated from a JavaScript array or a remote service, a data item is inserted, updated or removed, the data items are paged, sorted, filtered, or grouped.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the change event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a request to the remote service fails.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-push
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source receives a push notification or the pushCreate, pushUpdate, or pushDestroy methods are called.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the push event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-end
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestEnd event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-start
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestStart event.</param>

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: compare
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A JavaScript function for comparing the values. If the first argument is less than the second one, returns -1.; If both arguments are the same, returns 0. or If the first argument is greater than the second one, returns +1..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: html-attributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The HTML attributes of the table cell (<td>) that is rendered for the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: editable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether this column can be edited by the user.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: editor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Provides a way to specify a custom editing UI for the column. To create the editing UI, use the container parameter.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: expandable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the column will show the icons that are used for expanding and collapsing child rows. By default, the "title" column of the Gantt is expandable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: field
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field to which the column is bound. The value of this field is displayed by the column during data binding.The field name should be a valid Javascript identifier and should contain only alphanumeric characters (or "$" or "_"), and may not start with a digit.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format that is applied to the value before it is displayed. Takes the form "{0:format}" where "format" is a standard number format,custom number format, standard date format or a custom date format.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: header-attributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The HTML attributes of the table header cell (<th>) that is rendered for the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: header-template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column header content. By default, the value of the title column option is displayed in the column header cell.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: header-template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column header content. By default, the value of the title column option is displayed in the column header cell.
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for HeaderTemplate</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: hidden
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the Gantt will not display the column. By default, all columns are displayed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: menu
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the Gantt will display the column in the column menu. By default, the column menu includes all data-bound columns, that is, the ones with a set field option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: min-screen-width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The pixel screen width below which the column will be hidden. The setting takes precedence over the hidden setting and the two cannot not be used at the same time.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column content. The Gantt renders table rows (<tr>) which represent the data source items. Each table row consists of table cells (<td>) which represent the GanttList columns. By default, the HTML-encoded value of the field is displayed in the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column content. The Gantt renders table rows (<tr>) which represent the data source items. Each table row consists of table cells (<td>) which represent the GanttList columns. By default, the HTML-encoded value of the field is displayed in the column.
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for Template</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text that is displayed in the column header cell. If not set the field is used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The width of the column. Numeric values are treated as pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: update-interval
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The update interval of the "current time" marker, in milliseconds.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: confirmation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the Gantt will display a confirmation dialog when the user deletes a task or a dependency.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: create
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to create tasks.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: dependency-create
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to create dependencies.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: dependency-destroy
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to delete dependencies.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: drag-percent-complete
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to edit the percentComplete of the tasks.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: destroy
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to delete tasks.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: move
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to move tasks.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: planned-tasks
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the default pop-up editor of the Gantt will render the plannedStart and plannedEnd editors for the edited task.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: reorder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to reorder tasks in the task list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: resize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the user won't be able to resize tasks.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the editor.The template should contain elements whose name HTML attributes are set as the editable fields. This is how the Gantt will know which field to update. The other option is to use MVVM bindings in order to bind HTML elements to data item fields.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

            </summary>

Supported units are "mm", "cm", "in" and "pt"..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of the server side proxy which will stream the file to the end user.A proxy will be used when the browser isn't capable of saving files locally. Such browsers are IE version 9 and lower and Safari.The developer is responsible for implementing the server-side proxy.The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType: The MIME type of the file; base64: The base-64 encoded file content or fileName: The file name, as requested by the caller.. The proxy should return the decoded file with set "Content-Disposition" header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the data source would automatically save any changed data items by calling the sync method. By default, changes are not automatically saved.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: batch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will batch CRUD operation requests. For example, updating two data items would cause one HTTP request instead of two. By default, the data source makes a HTTP request for every CRUD operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: in-place-sort
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the original Array used as data will be sorted when sorting operation is performed. This setting supported only with local data, bound to a JavaScript array via the data option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: group-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will treat groups as items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: offline-storage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The offline storage key or custom offline storage implementation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page of data which the data source will return when the view method is invoked or request from the remote service.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page-size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of data items per page. The property has no default value. That is why to use paging, make sure some pageSize value is set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: accent-folding-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures whether diacritic filtering should be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source is populated from a JavaScript array or a remote service, a data item is inserted, updated or removed, the data items are paged, sorted, filtered, or grouped.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the change event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a request to the remote service fails.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-push
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source receives a push notification or the pushCreate, pushUpdate, or pushDestroy methods are called.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the push event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-end
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a remote service request is finished.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestEnd event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-start
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source makes a remote service request.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.It is possible to prevent the remote request. To achieve this, execute e.preventDefault() in the handler function.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestStart event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired after the data source saves data item changes. The data source saves the data item changes when the sync method is called.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the sync event.</param>

<summary>
            The URL of the server side proxy which will stream the file to the end user.A proxy will be used when the browser isn't capable of saving files locally. Such browsers are IE version 9 and lower and Safari.The developer is responsible for implementing the server-side proxy.The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType: The MIME type of the file; base64: The base-64 encoded file content or fileName: The file name, as requested by the caller.. The proxy should return the decoded file with the "Content-Disposition" header set toattachment; filename="<fileName.xslx>".

<summary>
            By default the grid will show the pager even when total amount of items in the DataSource is less than the pageSize.If set to false the grid will toggle the pager visibility as follows: when the total amount of items initially set in the DataSource is less than the pageSize number the pager will be hidden.; when the total amount of items initially set in the DataSource is greater than or equal to the pageSize number the pager will be shown.; when the total amount of items in the DataSource becomes less than the pageSize number (after delete, filter operation or pageSize change) the pager will be hidden. or when the total amount of items in the DataSource becomes greater than or equal to the pageSize number (after an insert, filter operation or pageSize change) the pager will be shown.. Introduced in the Kendo UI 2017 R3 release.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of data items which will be displayed in the grid. This setting will not work if the Grid is assigned an already existing Kendo UI DataSource instance.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position in which the grid pager will be rendered. Valid values are "top" and "bottom" (default).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: previous-next
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the pager will display buttons for going to the first, previous, next and last pages. By default those buttons are displayed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: refresh
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the pager will display the refresh button. Clicking the refresh button will refresh the grid. By default the refresh button is not displayed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: responsive
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false the pager will not be responsive. By default the pager is responsive.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: bottom
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The bottom margin. Numbers are considered as "pt" units.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: left
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The left margin. Numbers are considered as "pt" units.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: right
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The right margin. Numbers are considered as "pt" units.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: top
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The top margin. Numbers are considered as "pt" units.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: all-pages
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Exports all grid pages, starting from the first one.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: author
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The author of the PDF document.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-print
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies if the Print dialog should be opened immediately after loading the document.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: avoid-links
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A flag indicating whether to produce actual hyperlinks in the exported PDF file.It's also possible to pass a CSS selector as argument. All matching links will be ignored.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: creator
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The creator of the PDF document.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: date
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The date when the PDF document is created. Defaults to new Date().
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: file-name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the file name of the exported PDF file.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: force-proxy
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the content will be forwarded to proxyURL even if the browser supports saving files locally.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: jpeg-quality
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the quality of the images within the exported file, from 0 to 1.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: keep-png
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true all PNG images contained in the exported file will be kept in PNG format.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: keywords
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the keywords of the exported PDF file.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: landscape
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set to true to reverse the paper dimensions if needed such that width is the larger edge.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: paper-size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the paper size of the PDF document. The default "auto" means paper size is determined by content.Supported values: A predefined size: "A4", "A3" etc; An array of two numbers specifying the width and height in points (1pt = 1/72in) or An array of two strings specifying the width and height in units. Supported units are "mm", "cm", "in" and "pt"..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A piece of HTML to be included in each page.  Can be used to display headers and footers.  See the documentation in drawDOM.Available template variables include: * pageNum * totalPages
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A piece of HTML to be included in each page.  Can be used to display headers and footers.  See the documentation in drawDOM.Available template variables include: * pageNum * totalPages
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for Template</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: repeat-headers
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set this to true to repeat the grid headers on each page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: scale
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A scale factor.  In many cases, text size on screen will be too big for print, so you can use this option to scale down the output in PDF.  See the documentation in drawDOM.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of the server side proxy which will stream the file to the end user.A proxy will be used when the browser is not capable of saving files locally, for example, Internet Explorer 9 and Safari.The developer is responsible for implementing the server-side proxy.The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType: The MIME type of the file; base64: The base-64 encoded file content or fileName: The file name, as requested by the caller.. The proxy should return the decoded file with the "Content-Disposition" header set toattachment; filename="<fileName.pdf>".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A name or keyword indicating where to display the document returned from the proxy.If you want to display the document in a new window or iframe, the proxy should set the "Content-Disposition" header to inline; filename="<fileName.pdf>".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: subject
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the subject of the PDF file.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the title of the PDF file.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: columns
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the user could reorder the columns by dragging their header cells. By default reordering is disabled. Multi-level headers allow reordering only in same level.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: rows
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the user could reorder the rows by dragging them. By default reordering for rows is disabled. If the selectable option is enabled for rows only selected rows will can be dragged and reordered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: virtual
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures the grid virtualization settings. If set to true the grid will enable row virtualization and display a single page of data. Scrolling would just change the data which is currently displayed.Can also be set to the following string values: "rows" - enables virtualization of rows.; "columns" - enables virtualization of columns. or "rows, columns" - enables virtualization of both rows and columns..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: endless
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the grid will always display a single page of data. Scrolling to the end will load more items untill all items are displayed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: fields-extended
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines a list of fields which will be included in the search. If values for the property are not defined the grid will search in all column fields.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: fields
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines a list of fields which will be included in the search. If values for the property are not defined the grid will search in all column fields.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: allow-unsort
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the user can get the grid in unsorted state by clicking the sorted column header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: show-indexes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the user will see sort sequence indicators for sorted columns.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: initial-direction
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Determines the inital (from un-sorted to sorted state) sort direction. The supported values are asc and desc.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The sorting mode. If set to "single" the user can sort by one column. If set to "multiple" the user can sort by multiple columns. And the "mixed" mode enables you to sort in single mode when clicking and switch to multiple when holding ctrl key.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: datasource
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The Grid data source configuration
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: selectable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the selection type of the grid.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-bind
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false, the Grid will not bind to the data source during initialization, i.e. it will not call the fetch method of the dataSource instance. In such scenarios data binding will occur when the change event of the dataSource instance is fired. By default, autoBind is set to true and the widget will bind to the data source specified in the configuration.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: column-resize-handle-width

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: encode-titles

<summary>
            If set to true the column title will be HTML-encoded before it is displayed. If set to false the column title will be displayed as is.

BoundAttributes.Name: height

BoundAttributes.Name: loader-type

BoundAttributes.Name: navigatable

<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: persist-selection

<summary>
            If set to true, users can resize columns by dragging the edges (resize handles) of their header cells. As of Kendo UI Q1 2015, users can also auto-fit a column by double-clicking its resize handle. In this case the column will assume the smallest possible width, which allows the column content to fit without wrapping.By default, column resizing is disabled.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the data source would automatically save any changed data items by calling the sync method. By default, changes are not automatically saved.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: batch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will batch CRUD operation requests. For example, updating two data items would cause one HTTP request instead of two. By default, the data source makes a HTTP request for every CRUD operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: in-place-sort

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source is populated from a JavaScript array or a remote service, a data item is inserted, updated or removed, the data items are paged, sorted, filtered, or grouped.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the change event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a request to the remote service fails.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.

            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-end

<summary>
            Fired when a remote service request is finished.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestEnd event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-start
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source makes a remote service request.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.It is possible to prevent the remote request. To achieve this, execute e.preventDefault() in the handler function.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestStart event.</param>

            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the sync event.</param>

Accepts letters and digits only.; a - Alphanumeric or space. Accepts letters, digits and space only.; . - Decimal placeholder. The decimal separator will be gotten from the current culture used by Kendo.; , - Thousands placeholder.             If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source is populated from a JavaScript array or a remote service, a data item is inserted, updated or removed, the data items are paged, sorted, filtered, or grouped.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.

            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the change event.</param>

<summary>
