            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: parse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Executed before the server response is used. Use it to preprocess or parse the server response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: total
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains the total number of data items. Can be set to a function which is called to return the total number of data items for the response.

BoundAttributes.Name: total-handler
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The type of the response.The supported values are: "xml"  or "json". By default, the schema interprets the server response as JSON.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the data source would automatically save any changed data items by calling the sync method. By default, changes are not automatically saved.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: batch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will batch CRUD operation requests. For example, updating two data items would cause one HTTP request instead of two. By default, the data source makes a HTTP request for every CRUD operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: in-place-sort
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the original Array used as data will be sorted when sorting operation is performed. This setting supported only with local data, bound to a JavaScript array via the data option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: group-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will treat groups as items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: offline-storage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The offline storage key or custom offline storage implementation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page of data which the data source will return when the view method is invoked or request from the remote service.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page-size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of data items per page. The property has no default value. That is why to use paging, make sure some pageSize value is set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: accent-folding-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures whether diacritic filtering should be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source is populated from a JavaScript array or a remote service, a data item is inserted, updated or removed, the data items are paged, sorted, filtered, or grouped.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the change event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a request to the remote service fails.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-push
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source receives a push notification or the pushCreate, pushUpdate, or pushDestroy methods are called.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the push event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-end
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a remote service request is finished.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestEnd event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-start
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source makes a remote service request.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.It is possible to prevent the remote request. To achieve this, execute e.preventDefault() in the handler function.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestStart event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired after the data source saves data item changes. The data source saves the data item changes when the sync method is called.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the sync event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: cache
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false, the request result will not be cached by the browser. Setting cache to false will only work correctly with HEAD and GET requests. It works by appending "_={timestamp}" to the GET parameters. By default, "jsonp" requests are not cached.Refer to the jQuery.ajax documentation for further information.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: content-type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The content-type HTTP header sent to the server. The default is "application/x-www-form-urlencoded". Use "application/json" if the content is JSON. Refer to the jQuery.ajax documentation for further information.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: datatype
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The type of result expected from the server. Commonly used values are "json" and "jsonp".Refer to the jQuery.ajax documentation for further information.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The type of request to make ("POST", "GET", "PUT" or "DELETE"). The default request is "GET".Refer to the jQuery.ajax documentation for further information.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: data
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: headers

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: cache
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: parameter-map
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The function which converts the request parameters to a format suitable for the remote service. By default, the data source sends the parameters using jQuery's conventions.If a transport.read.data function is used together with parameterMap, do not forget to preserve the result from the data function that will be received in the parameterMap arguments. An example is provided below. Generally, the parameterMap function is designed to transform the request payload, not add new parameters to it.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: submit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A function that will handle create, update and delete operations in a single batch when custom transport is used, i.e. the transport.read is defined as a function.The transport.create, transport.update and transport.delete operations will not be executed in this case.
            </summary>

<summary>

The default "auto" means paper size is determined by content.Supported values: A predefined size: "A4", "A3" etc; An array of two numbers specifying the width and height in points (1pt = 1/72in) or An array of two strings specifying the width and height in units. Supported units are "mm", "cm", "in" and "pt"..

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

The proxy should return the decoded file with the "Content-Disposition" header set toattachment; filename="<fileName.pdf>".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-target

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-refresh
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

<summary>
            Specifies the paper size of the PDF document. The default "auto" means paper size is determined by content.Supported values: A predefined size: "A4", "A3" etc; An array of two numbers specifying the width and height in points (1pt = 1/72in) or An array of two strings specifying the width and height in units. Supported units are "mm", "cm", "in" and "pt"..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of the server side proxy which will stream the file to the end user.A proxy will be used when the browser isn't capable of saving files locally. Such browsers are IE version 9 and lower and Safari.The developer is responsible for implementing the server-side proxy.The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType: The MIME type of the file; base64: The base-64 encoded file content or fileName: The file name, as requested by the caller.. The proxy should return the decoded file with set "Content-Disposition" header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A name or keyword indicating where to display the document returned from the proxy.If you want to display the document in a new window or iframe, the proxy should set the "Content-Disposition" header to inline; filename="<fileName.pdf>".
            </summary>

The proxy will return the decoded file with the Content-Disposition header set to attachment; filename="<fileName.pdf>".The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType - The MIME type of the file.; base64 - The base-64 encoded file content. or fileName - The file name as requested by the caller..

BoundAttributes.Name: use-culture-decimals
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the Spreadsheet formula parser will obey the decimal separator of the current culture.  If set to false (default), the decimal separator in formulas will always be the dot.This flag has implications on how formulas are entered. When it is set to true, in cultures where the decimal separator is the comma (,), similar to Excel, the following additional changes upon entering a formula will occur: The semicolon will become a function argument separator. For example, =SUM(A1;A2) instead of =SUM(A1,A2). or The backslash will become an element separator in an array formula. For example, ={1\2;3\4} instead of ={1,2;3,4}.. This flag only affects the presentation - the way formulas are entered by the end user or displayed on screen. Serialization to JSON or XLSX as well as the public API functions will continue to use the dot as decimal separator and the comma as an argument separator (canonical form). For example, to apply a formula by using the API, even if useCultureDecimals is in effect, you still need to use the canonical form.To make the API functions obey useCultureDecimals, wrap your code in a call to sheet.withCultureDecimals. Assuming a culture where the comma is used for decimals, compare the previous example with the following one.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-show

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-hide
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies if the Tooltip will be hidden when the mouse leaves the target element. If set to false, a Close button will be shown within Tooltip. If set to false, showAfter is specified, and showOn is set to mouseenter, the Tooltip will be displayed after the given timeout even if the element is no longer hovered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: callout
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies if the Tooltip callout will be displayed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: filter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a selector for the elements within the container which will display the Tooltip.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: iframe
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The width (in pixels) of the Tooltip.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The position that is relative to the target element at which the Tooltip will be shown.The supported values are: bottom; top; left; right or center.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: show-after
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the delay (in milliseconds) before the Tooltip shows. This option is ignored if showOn is set to click or focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: show-on
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event on which the Tooltip will be shown.The supported values are: mouseenter; click or focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: hide-after
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the delay (in milliseconds) before the Tooltip is hidden.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: offset
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the offset (in pixels) between the Tooltip and the anchor. If the callout property is set to true, the offset is rendered from the callout arrow. If the callout property is set to false, the offset is rendered from the content of the Tooltip.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text which result will be shown within the Tooltip. By default the Tooltip will display the target element title attribute content.
            </summary>

<summary>
            The field from the response which contains the aggregate results. Can be set to a function which is called to return the aggregate results from the response.The result of the function should be a JavaScript object which contains the aggregate results for every field in the following format:For example, if the data source is configured like this:The aggregate results should have the following format:
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the response which contains the aggregate results. Can be set to a function which is called to return the aggregate results from the response.The result of the function should be a JavaScript object which contains the aggregate results for every field in the following format:For example, if the data source is configured like this:The aggregate results should have the following format:
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: data
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains the data items. Can be set to a function which is called to return the data items for the response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: datahandler
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains the data items. Can be set to a function which is called to return the data items for the response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: errors
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains server-side errors. Can be set to a function which is called to return the errors for response. If there are any errors, the error event will be fired.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: errors-handler
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains server-side errors. Can be set to a function which is called to return the errors for response. If there are any errors, the error event will be fired.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: groups
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains the groups. Can be set to a function which is called to return the groups from the response.The result should have the following format:
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: groups-handler
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains the groups. Can be set to a function which is called to return the groups from the response.The result should have the following format:
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: parse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Executed before the server response is used. Use it to preprocess or parse the server response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: total
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains the total number of data items. Can be set to a function which is called to return the total number of data items for the response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: total-handler
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field from the server response which contains the total number of data items. Can be set to a function which is called to return the total number of data items for the response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The type of the response.The supported values are: "xml"  or "json". By default, the schema interprets the server response as JSON.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the data source would automatically save any changed data items by calling the sync method. By default, changes are not automatically saved.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: batch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will batch CRUD operation requests. For example, updating two data items would cause one HTTP request instead of two. By default, the data source makes a HTTP request for every CRUD operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: in-place-sort
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the original Array used as data will be sorted when sorting operation is performed. This setting supported only with local data, bound to a JavaScript array via the data option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: group-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will treat groups as items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: offline-storage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The offline storage key or custom offline storage implementation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page of data which the data source will return when the view method is invoked or request from the remote service.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: page-size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of data items per page. The property has no default value. That is why to use paging, make sure some pageSize value is set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: accent-folding-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Configures whether diacritic filtering should be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-aggregates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the aggregate calculation to the remote service. By default, the data source calculates aggregates client-side.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-filtering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the filtering implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs filtering client-side.By default, the filter is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the filter { logic: "and", filters: [ { field: "name", operator: "startswith", value: "Jane" } ] } is sent as: filter[logic]: and; filter[filters][0][field]: name; filter[filters][0][operator]: startswith or filter[filters][0][value]: Jane. Use the parameterMap option to send the filter option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-grouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the grouping implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs grouping client-side.By default, the group is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the group { field: "category", dir: "desc" } is sent as: group[0][field]: category or group[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the group option in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-paging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item paging implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs paging client-side.The following options are sent to the server when server paging is enabled: page - the page of data item to return (1 means the first page).; pageSize - the number of items to return.; skip - how many data items to skip. or take - the number of data items to return (the same as pageSize).. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: server-sorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the data source will leave the data item sorting implementation to the remote service. By default, the data source performs sorting client-side.By default, the sort is sent to the server following jQuery's conventions.For example, the sort { field: "age", dir: "desc" } is sent as: sort[0][field]: age or sort[0][dir]: desc. Use the parameterMap option to send the paging options in a different format.For more information and tips about client and server data operations, refer to the introductory article on the DataSource.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-change
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source is populated from a JavaScript array or a remote service, a data item is inserted, updated or removed, the data items are paged, sorted, filtered, or grouped.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the change event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a request to the remote service fails.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-push
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source receives a push notification or the pushCreate, pushUpdate, or pushDestroy methods are called.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the push event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-end
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when a remote service request is finished.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestEnd event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-request-start
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the data source makes a remote service request.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.It is possible to prevent the remote request. To achieve this, execute e.preventDefault() in the handler function.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the requestStart event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-sync
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired after the data source saves data item changes. The data source saves the data item changes when the sync method is called.The event handler function context (available via the this keyword) will be set to the data source instance.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the sync event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: class-name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The CSS class that is applied to the command button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: image-class
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The CSS class that is applied to the icon span of the command button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: click
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The JavaScript function that is executed when the user clicks the command button. The function receives a jQuery event as an argument. The function context that is available through the this keyword will be set to the TreeList instance.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the command. Commands can be built-in ("edit", "createChild" and "destroy") or custom. When set to a custom value, the name is rendered as a data-command attribute. For more information, refer to the columns.command section.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: text
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text that is displayed by the command button. If not set, the name option is used as the button text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ui
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The role data attribute of the widget that is used in the filter menu, or a JavaScript function which initializes that widget.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: columns
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text message that is displayed for the column selection menu item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: filter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text message that is displayed for the filter menu item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: sort-ascending
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text message that is displayed for the menu item which performs the ascending sort mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: sort-descending
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text message that is displayed for the menu item which performs the descending sort mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: settings
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text message that is displayed in the menu header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: lock
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text message that is displayed in the column menu when locking a column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: unlock
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text message that is displayed in the column menu for unlocking a column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: columns
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the column menu allows the user to select (show and hide) TreeList columns. By default, the column menu allows column selection.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: filterable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the column menu will allow the user to filter the TreeList. By default, if filtering is enabled through filterable, the column menu allows the user to filter.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: sortable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the column menu will allow the user to sort the TreeList by the column field. By default, if sorting is enabled through sortable, the column menu allows the user to sort the data.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: compare
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A JavaScript function for comparing the values. If the first argument is less than the second one, returns -1.; If both arguments are the same, returns 0. or If the first argument is greater than the second one, returns +1..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: html-attributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The HTML attributes of the table cell (<td>) that is rendered for the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: editable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The JavaScript function that is executed when the cell or row is about to be opened for editing. The returned result will determine whether an editor for the column will be created.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: editor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Provides a way to specify a custom editing UI for the column. To create the editing UI, use the container parameter.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: encoded
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the column value will be HTML-encoded before it is displayed. If set to false, the column value will be displayed as is. By default, the column value is HTML-encoded.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: expandable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the column will show the icons that are used for expanding and collapsing child rows. By default, the first column of the TreeList is expandable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: field
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The field to which the column is bound. The value of this field is displayed by the column during data binding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: footer-template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the footer table cell for the column.The following fields can be used in the template: average - The value of the average aggregate (if specified).; count - The value of the count aggregate (if specified).; max - The value of the max aggregate (if specified).; min - The value of the min aggregate (if specified). or sum - The value of the sum aggregate (if specified)..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: footer-template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the footer table cell for the column.The following fields can be used in the template: average - The value of the average aggregate (if specified).; count - The value of the count aggregate (if specified).; max - The value of the max aggregate (if specified).; min - The value of the min aggregate (if specified). or sum - The value of the sum aggregate (if specified)..
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for FooterTemplate</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format that is applied to the value before it is displayed. Takes the {0:format} form where format is a standard number format, custom number format, standard date format or a custom date format.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: header-attributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The HTML attributes of the table header cell (<th>) that is rendered for the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: header-template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column header content. By default, the value of the title column option is displayed in the column header cell.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: header-template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column header content. By default, the value of the title column option is displayed in the column header cell.
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for HeaderTemplate</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: min-screen-width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The pixel screen width below which the column will be hidden. The setting takes precedence over the hidden setting and the two cannot not be used at the same time.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: selectable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the treelist will render a select column with checkboxes in each cell, thus enabling multi-row selection. The header checkbox allows users to select/deselect all the rows on the current page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column content. The TreeList renders table rows (<tr>) which represent the data source items. Each table row consists of table cells (<td>) which represent the TreeList columns. By default, the HTML-encoded value of the field is displayed in the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the column content. The TreeList renders table rows (<tr>) which represent the data source items. Each table row consists of table cells (<td>) which represent the TreeList columns. By default, the HTML-encoded value of the field is displayed in the column.
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for Template</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text that is displayed in the column header cell. If not set, the TreeList uses field.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The width of the column. Numeric values are treated as pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: hidden
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the TreeList will not display the column. By default, all columns are displayed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: include-children
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the TreeList will select all child rows upon parent row selection when checkbox selection is used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: menu
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the TreeList will display the column in the column menu. By default, the column menu includes all data-bound columns, that is, the ones with a set field option.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: locked
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the TreeList will display the column as locked (frozen).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: lockable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to false, the column will remain in that side of the TreeList where its own locked configuration placed it.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: reorderable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables reordering of rows via a drag-and-drop UI.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the popup editor.The template has to contain elements whose name HTML attribute is set to the name of the editable field. In this way, the TreeList recognizes the field to which it has to bind the each editor. Alternatively, use MVVM bindings for binding HTML elements to data item fields.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the popup editor.The template has to contain elements whose name HTML attribute is set to the name of the editable field. In this way, the TreeList recognizes the field to which it has to bind the each editor. Alternatively, use MVVM bindings for binding HTML elements to data item fields.
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for Template</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents the editing modes supported by Kendo UI TreeList for ASP.NET MVC
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: all-pages
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the TreeList will export all pages of data. By default the TreeList exports only the current page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: file-name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the file name of the exported Excel file.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: filterable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables column filtering in the Excel file. Not to be mistaken with the filtering feature of the TreeList.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: force-proxy
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the content will be forwarded to proxyURL even if the browser supports local file saving.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: proxy-url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of the server-side proxy which will stream the file to the end user. A proxy will be used when the browser is not capable of saving files locally. Such browsers are IE version 9 and earlier and Safari. The developer is responsible for implementing the server-side proxy. The proxy will return the decoded file with the Content-Disposition header set to attachment; filename="<fileName.xslx>".The proxy will receive a POST request with the following parameters in the request body: contentType - The MIME type of the file.; base64 - The base-64 encoded file content. or fileName - The file name as requested by the caller..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: and
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the option which represents the AND logical operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: clear
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the button which clears the filter.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: filter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the button which applies the filter.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: info
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the information message on top of the filter menu.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text that is rendered for the title attribute of the filter menu form.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: is-false
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the radio button for false values. Displayed when the user filters Boolean fields.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: is-true
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the radio button for true values. Displayed when the user filters Boolean fields.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: or
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the option which represents the OR logical operation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: eq
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the eq (equal to) filter operator.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: neq
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the ne (not equal to) filter operator.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: isnull
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the isnull filter operator.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: isnotnull
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the isnotnull filter operator.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: gte
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the gte (greater than or equal to) filter operator.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: gt
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the gt (greater than) filter operator.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: lte
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the "lte" (less than or equal to) filter operator.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: lt
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text of the lt (less than) filter operator.

<summary>
            By default and if supported by the browser, the selected files are uploaded in separate requests. To change this behavior, set batch to true. As a result, all selected files are uploaded in one request.The batch mode applies to multiple files which are selected simultaneously. Files that are selected one after the other are uploaded in separate requests.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: chunk-size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When async.chunkSize is set, the selected files are uploaded chunk by chunk with the declared size. Each request sends a separate file blob and additional string metadata to the server. This metadata is in a stringified JSON format and contains the fileName, relativePath, chunkIndex, contentType, totalFileSize, totalChunks, and uploadUid properties. These properties enable the validation and combination of the file on the server side. The response also returns a JSON object with the uploaded and fileUid properties, which notifies the client what the next chunk is.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: concurrent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            By default, the selected files are uploaded one after the other. When async.concurrent is set to true, all selected files start to upload simultaneously.
            </summary>

            Triggered when a Window has finished its opening animation.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the activate event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-close
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when a Window is closed either by the user or through the close() method.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the close event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-deactivate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when a Window has finished its closing animation.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the deactivate event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-dragend
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when a Window has been moved by the user.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the dragend event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-dragstart
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the user starts to move the Window.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the dragstart event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when an Ajax request for content fails.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-maximize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the user maximizes the Window. Introduced in 2016.Q1.SP1.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the maximize event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-minimize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the user minimizes the Window. Introduced in 2016.Q1.SP1.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the minimize event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-open
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when a Window is opened, that is, when the open() method is called.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the open event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-refresh
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the content of a Window has finished loading via Ajax, when the Window iframe has finished loading, or when the Refresh button has been clicked on a Window with static content.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the refresh event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-resize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the user resizes the Window.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the resize event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-restore
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the Window is restored to its previous state(maximized or minimized) by pressing the restore button, or when the restore() method is called.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the restore event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: auto-focus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Determines whether the Window will be focused automatically when opened. The property also influences the focus behavior when an already opened Window is clicked.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: iframe
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Explicitly states whether a content iframe will be created. For more information, refer to the documentation on using iframes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: pinned
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Window will be pinned, that is, that it will not move together with the page content during scrolling.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: scrollable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables (true) or disables (false) the scrolling of the Window contents.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Window will be initially visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets a predefined size to the Window. The width and height configuration options override the predefined size.The supported values are: auto; small; medium or large.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: resizable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables the ability for users to resize a Window.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: append-to
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The element that the Window will be appended to.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: text
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text in the window title bar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: encoded
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the title text should be encoded.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: done
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies text to be rendered in the "Done" button on the final step.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: next
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies text to be rendered in the "Next" button on each step.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: of
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies text to be rendered in the Pager element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: previous
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies text to be rendered in the "Previous" button on each step.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: reset
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies text to be rendered in the "Reset" button on each step.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: step
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies text to be rendered in the Pager element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: click
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A click handler that defines the logic to be executed upon button click.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Button in question is enabled or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the name of the Button. The default buttons have "reserved" names (those names are "previous", "next", "done", "reset"). That would allow additional customization of that Buttons' text and behavior.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: primary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Button will have the k-primary class assigned or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: text
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the text to be displayed in the Button.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Kendo.Mvc.TagHelpers.WizardStepContentTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Kendo UI Wizard Step Content TagHelper
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: indicator
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Stepper instance will display the indicators of its steps.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: label
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Stepper instance will display the labels of its steps.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: linear
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Stepper will allow non-linear navigation (selection of steps which are not immediately next to the current step).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: content-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the id of a DOM element, which content to be used as a content of the current step.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: content-url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies an endpoint which the step content should be loaded from.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: class-name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a custom class that will be set on the step container element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the step is enabled or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: icon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines a name of an existing icon in the Kendo UI theme sprite. The icon will be displayed in the Stepper step element. For a list of available icon names, please refer to the Web Font Icons article.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: icon-template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template used to render the icon in the Stepper step.The fields which can be used in the template are: title String - the title set on the step; label String - same as title - the title set on the step; icon String - the icon specified for this step (if any); enabled Boolean - indicates whether the step is enabled (true) or disabled (false); selected Boolean - indicates whether the step is selected; previous Boolean - indicates whether the step is before the currently selected or not; index Number - a zero-based index of the current step; isFirstStep Boolean - indicates whether the step is the initial one in the Stepper; isLastStep Boolean - indicates whether the step is the last one in the Stepper; indicatorVisible Boolean - indicates whether the indicator, which holds the icon should be displayed or not or labelVisible Boolean - indicates whether the label section of the step should be displayed or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: icon-template-id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template used to render the icon in the Stepper step.The fields which can be used in the template are: title String - the title set on the step; label String - same as title - the title set on the step; icon String - the icon specified for this step (if any); enabled Boolean - indicates whether the step is enabled (true) or disabled (false); selected Boolean - indicates whether the step is selected; previous Boolean - indicates whether the step is before the currently selected or not; index Number - a zero-based index of the current step; isFirstStep Boolean - indicates whether the step is the initial one in the Stepper; isLastStep Boolean - indicates whether the step is the last one in the Stepper; indicatorVisible Boolean - indicates whether the indicator, which holds the icon should be displayed or not or labelVisible Boolean - indicates whether the label section of the step should be displayed or not.
            </summary>
            <param name="value">The ID of the template element for IconTemplate</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: pager
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the pager will be rendered on the current step or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a title of the current step.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-activate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fires when a new step has been selected upon user interaction.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the activate event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-content-load
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when content is fetched from an AJAX request and has been loaded.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the contentLoad event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-done
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the "Done" action Button has been clicked
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the done event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-error
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when an attempt to fetch step content with an AJAX request fails. The event will be fired only when the user clicks on the Previous or Next button, or navigates to another step using the Stepper. It will not be fired if the remote request is raised as a result of a Step.load() method call.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the error event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-reset
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggered when the "Reset" action Button has been clicked
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the reset event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-select
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fires when the user clicks on the Stepper or clicks on "Previous"/"Next" action Buttons to select another step.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the select event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: on-form-validate-failed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fired when the validateForms configuration option is set to true (default), and the validation of the Kendo UI Form on the current Wizard step fails when the user tries to navigate to another step.
            </summary>
            <param name="handler">The name of the JavaScript function that will handle the formValidateFailed event.</param>

BoundAttributes.Name: action-bar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the Steps in the Wizard will render their Buttons and Pager element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: load-on-demand
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the step content will be loaded on demand when a given step is selected. Applicable when the step configuration has "contentUrl" set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: pager
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the Steps in the Wizard will render their Pager element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: reload-on-select
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the step content will be reloaded on each navigation to given step. Applicable when the step configuration has "contentUrl" set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: content-position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The position of the Wizard step content according to the embedded Stepper widget.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: validate-on-previous
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether navigation to previous Step will trigger current Step Form validation. By default, Form validation is enabled for any step navigation.
            </summary>

            </summary>

            <value>Defaults to <c>false</c> if user provides an <c>action</c> attribute
            or if the <c>method</c> is <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.FormMethod.Get" />; <c>true</c> otherwise.</value>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-route

            Name of the route.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Must be <c>null</c> if <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.FormTagHelper.Action" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.FormTagHelper.Controller" /> is non-<c>null</c>.
            </remarks>

            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Razor.TagHelpers.UrlResolutionTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting elements containing attributes with URL expected values.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Resolves URLs starting with '~/' (relative to the application's 'webroot' setting) that are not
            targeted by other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s. Runs prior to other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s to ensure
            application-relative URLs are resolved.</remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: get
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for binding the value to the attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: set
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for updating the bound value when a new value is available.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: after
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies an action to run after the new value has been set.
